# CompanyScope coding standards

## General
- Prefer clarity over cleverness
- Use small, composable modules
- Keep business logic out of UI components
- Add docstrings or comments where intent is not obvious
- Keep naming consistent with docs and API contracts

## TypeScript standards
- Use strict TypeScript
- Avoid `any`
- Validate external data with Zod or shared schemas
- Keep React components focused and accessible
- Use TanStack Query for server state

## Python standards
- Use Pydantic models for request and response validation
- Use SQLAlchemy for persistence
- Keep parser logic pure where possible
- Use Decimal for monetary values, not float
- Separate extraction, mapping, validation, and persistence concerns

## API and schema discipline
- Align endpoint names and payloads with `docs/03-api-spec.md`
- Align financial fact naming with `docs/02-database-schema.md`
- Preserve provenance fields on extracted data
- Use consistent error response shapes

## Testing expectations
- Add or update tests for meaningful behaviour changes
- Parser changes should include fixture or golden test updates
- New signals should include triggering and non-triggering tests
- Avoid merging major logic without at least unit and integration coverage

## Security standards
- Never expose secrets client-side
- Never log sensitive secret values
- Validate all incoming parameters
- Rate-limit public-facing search and refresh endpoints
